==History==
==History==
The Newport Opera House was built in 1886 after the previous Town Hall and COurthouse burnt down in 1885. The rebuilt Opera House was noted to have the largest stage North of Boston, Mass. 1974 began the restoration of the Opera House, and concluded with the unveiling of the stage in 1976 with its opening production of THE MUSIC MAN. It currently stands as a landmark and a fully functioning theatre in the center of [[Newport, NH]] in [[Sullivan County]].
